ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Stick to your treatment plan even when side effects begin to interfere with daily activities?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Integrate your treatment into your daily routine?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Integrate your treatment into your daily routine even if it means taking medication or doing other things in front of people who don't know you are HIV-positive?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Stick to your treatment schedule even when your daily routine is disrupted?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Stick to your treatment schedule when you aren't feeling well?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Stick to your treatment schedule when it means changing your eating habits?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Continue with your treatment even if doing so interferes with your daily activities?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Continue with the treatment plan your physician prescribed even if your T-cells drop significantly in the next three months?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Continue with your treatment even when you are feeling discouraged about your health?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Continue with your treatment even when getting to your clinic appointments is a major hassle?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Continue with your treatment even when people close to you tell you that they don't think that it is doing any good?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do

ElementDescription: In the past month, how confident have you been that you could: Get something positive out of your participation in treatment, even if the medication you are taking does not improve your health?
Notes: 0=Cannot do at all; 5=Moderately certain can do; 10=Completely certain can do
